                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d825">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39) City of Flint/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-28T03:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 28, 1939—3 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 28—1:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>822. I have learned that the German Embassy has received information from
                    Murmansk that the German prize crew was put back on board the <hi rend="italic"
                        >City of Flint</hi> yesterday. I further understand that members of that
                    Embassy are expressing their conviction that the <hi rend="italic">City of
                        Flint</hi> will be successfully brought to a German port by remaining within
                    Scandinavian territorial waters on the voyage from Murmansk to Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
